-- HSBC, Poste Italiane Form Money Transfer Accord, Pre-Paid Cards, Sole Says
-- Armorel Kenna
-- 2010-06-18T06:19:52Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-18/hsbc-poste-italiane-form-money-transfer-venture-pre-paid-cards-sole-says.html

          
          
             HSBC Holdings plc and Poste Italiane
signed a partnership for money transfers and cross-border pre
payments, daily Il Sole 24 Ore reported, citing company
executives.  
 “We are an ideal partner for any type of cross-order
business for Italian companies that want to seize opportunities
in countries that drive the growth of the global economy,”
HSBC’s Italy Chief Executive Officer Marzio Perrelli said,
according to the Italian newspaper, also citing his counterpart
at Poste Italiane.  
 BancoPosta account holders can transfer money outside the
euro area using HSBC’s network, Il Sole reported.  
 HSBC has also presented a joint offer to the Indian
government, which is seeking a partner for pre-paid cards at its
post offices, Il Sole reported.  
